In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 25, 2016, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day. He acknowledges the sacrifices made by Gold Star families, who have lost loved ones in military service, and emphasizes the importance of supporting them. Obama calls on government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold ceremonies to show gratitude and respect for these families. The article also mentions that the last Sunday in September has been designated as "Gold Star Mother's Day" by Congress since 1936.